23/ I am unable to sleep, I am so beyond words for what has transpired and the negligence of your company. This will be blasted throughout social media, as I cannot believe the level of indecency and dismissal. @Airbnb @Airbnbdesign

22/ We are still stranded with nowhere to go, trying not to throw up from the stress. (Update: in the time it took me to type this, one of us has actually vomited from the stress) Airbnb has left two honest, paying customers with a bogus reservation and no concern for reconciling

21/ It’s 2am the middle of the night, and nobody seems to care about what has happened here. I cannot believe that we managed to speak to Rita herself - who deserves an explanation as well… -and she was so incredibly gracious to let us stay with her as long as she did @Airbnb

20/ at this point, this is a full on crisis. We are literally crashing on a guest bed we have no right to stay in by the kindness of a Good Samaritan. I’ve sent over a dozen messages to @Airbnb since with no response at all. NONE
19/ she ends up hanging up but only after assuring me it’s just to call Rita and she’d call me right back after she’s done. It’s been 7 hours. No call. NO CALL BACK. @Airbnb @AirbnbHelp

18/ I pleaded to not hang up with someone. The 844 number is disconnected and cannot be reached by phone here so I didn’t have any other options. I was in a (very nice) stranger’s house overstaying my welcome and I was becoming lightheaded from lack of sleep and food and water.

17/ Rose then says that she never called the host and is going to hang up on me to do that after I was put on hold before for the exact same thing. Then she said she didn’t do it because I told her not to (?????!!!!) @Airbnb @AirbnbHelp

16/ I then began to realize that nobody I was speaking with cared that the sun was setting and I had nowhere to sleep. Nobody cared that I was terrified and I was promised a bed and a toilet and a shower, and I would get none of those things. @Airbnb @AirbnbHelp
15/ like at this point I’ve been on the phone for almost two hours for two different team members to say the exact same thing and blow me off. @Airbnb @AirbnbHelp

14/ rose said nah She still needed to call. put on hold again and THEN she said that she’ll hang up with me, submit this case and review it and have someone call me back within an hour or two, the same thing Michael told me when the situation is deemed “very serious and urgent”

13/ the host “Rita” never got our calls because her # is no longer in service, which I told Rose @ Airbnb. She said she still needed to call to make sure it was dead. Since I was actually sitting right next to Rita, I told Rose that she could just talk to her right now …

12/ I eventually got connected with Rose from the Resolutions team. Rose repeated almost verbatim that this was a very urgent and serious matter and needed to be dealt with immediately. Rose then told me that she needed to put me on a brief hold so she could call the host.

11/ I was scared and feeling very duped and dismissed. I insisted I stay on the line as I do not want to be disconnected as I do not trust that I will get a call back. He obliged (with some mild resistance, a frustration in its own right, as I needed help and didn’t feel safe)

10/ He comes back after about 3 or 4 two-minute holds and tells me that the Resolutions team is overloaded with calls and he would have to hang up and have them call me “within about an hour or two.” I was stunned, how could an urgent and serious matter be pushed off for hour(s)?

9/ I speak to Michael and explain how we are stranded here in Mexico and we have a confirmed reservation that we paid for. He is alarmed and assured me this is a “very serious and urgent matter” and it will be dealt with right away.

8/ we go in and she says we are welcome to stay until we can figure out somewhere else to go. I’m thinking… OH GOD. WHERE ARE WE GOING TO SLEEP??  Sun is setting. I call Airbnb and their 844 number is unreachable here. I message on the app. I get a call within minutes

7/ she says she never approved our reservation, never got notified, nothing. Has no idea why her whole ass person and house are on Airbnb?? She hasn’t hosted in years. She invites us in to sort the whole thing out. We are… hesitant. Who got paid tho? But we didn’t have options

6/ we end up saying “wait what…” and knock on her door again. Start chatting her up. She looks at the listing and is like wait, that’s my house! My face! My personal bio! What the hell? I haven’t had an Airbnb guest since February of 2020! I haven’t even been in Mexico either!

5/ (sorry numbering fucked up)

Someone happens to leave so we jump inside so we aren’t on the street. We go up the stairs and stand on the landing. Calls, texts. Nothing. Where is our host??? What is going on?? We start asking if anyone passing knows “Rita” (not her real name 4 privacy). No luck
